Package: pre
Title: Prediction rule ensembles
Version: 0.1.0.0000
Authors@R: person("Marjolein", "Fokkema", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "m.fokkema@fsw.leidenuniv.nl")
Author: Marjolein Fokkema [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Marjolein Fokkema <m.fokkema@fsw.leidenuniv.nl>
Description: An R package for deriving prediction rule ensembles (PREs). The package largely follows the procedure for deriving PREs as described in Friedman & Popescu (2008; DOI:10.1214/07-AOAS148), with several adjustments and improvements. The main function is pre(), which derives a prediction rule ensemble. Functions predict(), coef() and importance() can be used to inspect the generated ensemble. Singeplot() and pairplot() depict partial dependence of the output on the predictor variables. Function cvpre() performs full cross validation of a upre to calculates the expected prediction error. Functions interact() and bsnullinteract() can be used to assess interaction effects of predictor variables.
Depends: R (>= 3.3.0), akima, partykit, glmnet, MatrixModels, Formula, methods, graphics
License: GPL-2 | GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
